This service vendors source code from ByteDance's LatentSync project.

Upstream:   https://github.com/bytedance/LatentSync
Commit:     a229c39 (snapshot at PR-LS-1c)
License:    Apache License 2.0 (see LICENSE in the upstream repo)

Vendored subtree lives under ``app/latentsync/`` (models, pipelines,
whisper, utils) and ``app/configs/`` (unet/stage2.yaml,
scheduler_config.json). Each file retains its original copyright
headers from ByteDance.

CPU adaptations applied to the vendored code are marked inline with a
"CPU patch:" comment. Summary of changes:

  - app/latentsync/pipelines/lipsync_pipeline.py
      ImageProcessor device changed from hard-coded "cuda" to
      self._execution_device (line ~342).

  - app/latentsync/utils/face_detector.py
      FaceDetector routes through onnxruntime's CPUExecutionProvider
      (and InsightFace ctx_id=-1) when device is not a cuda:* string.

  - app/latentsync/utils/image_processor.py
      Removed the "face detection on CPU is not supported" guard now
      that FaceDetector handles CPU.

  - app/latentsync/utils/affine_transform.py
      AlignRestore dtype default changed from torch.float16 to
      torch.float32. fp16 CPU kernels are partial and noisy; float32
      is the safe CPU default.

  - app/latentsync/models/unet.py
    app/latentsync/whisper/whisper/__init__.py
      torch.cuda.empty_cache() calls guarded behind
      torch.cuda.is_available() so they no-op on CPU-only hosts.

Weight downloads (app/scripts/download_models.sh) pull from
https://huggingface.co/ByteDance/LatentSync-1.6. The weights carry
their own license terms as published on that HF page; consult them
before any commercial redistribution.
